SUMMARY:In-Person Cultural Arts Trip - "The Best of Broadway: Mostly Musicals"
DESCRIPTION:Join in this delightful trip to enjoy seven of Bway’s hottest shows\, “behind-the-curtain” meetings w/theater pros\, sumptuous meals & more!\n\n\n\n\n\n\nGive your regards to Broadway with a musical journey to the “city that never sleeps!” \n  \nHead to NYC which is bustling with the excitement of countless shows and with the anticipation of the Tony Awards. Join in this trip to see seven – yes\, seven! – of Broadway’s hottest shows – mostly musicals! \n  \nCheck into the InterContinental Times Square for a 6-night stay at this lovely hotel\, conveniently located in the Theater District. \n  \nThree exclusive “Behind-the-Scenes” discussions with Broadway professionals not only offer personal insights into the lives of those in the theater community\, but also are sure to be a highlight of trip! New in 2026! One of these events will be a private meeting with a Broadway Dresser and a “Quick Change” workshop! \n  \nEnjoy sumptuous meals in some of the Theater Districts culinary gems! \n  \n…and more! \n  \nCome for the delightful musicals! Leave with memories of great shows\, interesting “behind the scenes” discussions\, delicious meals\, and more! \n  \nFor Details & Pricing\, email James at jsokol@marinjcc.org with “B’way Trip Info Request” in the subject line. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Cultural Arts Trips offered by the National JCC Adult & Senior Alliance & the Osher Marin JCC are open to all. \nJCC Members and non-members; people of all backgrounds & faiths\, hair styles and chocolate preferences are invited to join in these enriching & delicious cultural programs! \n  \n\n\n\n\nOur group after another exclusive “behind-the-scenes” meeting…this time\, with Jerrod Spector\, who starred as Frankie Valli for four years of the Broadway run in Jersey Boys\, was Tony-nominated for his role as Barry Mann in Beautiful: The Carole King Musical\, and recently played Sonny Bono in Broadway’s The Cher Show\, and is currently starring at King George III in Hamilton.\n\n\n  \nFor information on this and other upcoming In-Person Cultural Arts Trips as well as on Online Programs\, click here
URL:https://www.marinjcc.org/event/the-best-of-broadway-mostly-musicals/
LOCATION:InterContinental Times Square\, Various Broadway Theaters\, Etc.\, 300 W 44th St\, New York\, NY\, 10036\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adult Learning
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/avif:https://www.marinjcc.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/https___cdn.evbuc_.com_images_532085849_44784881969_1_original-1.avif
END:VEVENT
